args: Rngh! How many times are these things\ngonna get back up?!
We're here! Everybody still in one piece?
Yes, but our enemies' attacks grow ever\nfiercer.

▷They haven't even started, from the look
of it. I thought it strange how soon they
reengaged. They were deployed without
any repairs.◁
It's like they don't give a damn about the\nandroids' condition...
Their movements communicate as much.\nIt's difficult to defend when they attack\nwithout regard for their own life and limb.
Not difficult. Impossible. And so this place\nwill be your tomb.
Is that the faerie Mascula saw?! Finally\ndecided to show your ugly mug, did ya?
Their signal receivers have likely not\nundergone maintenance either. I surmise\nthey can't be remote controlled.
So the wirepuller is as desperate as his\npuppets. I suppose this is as close as they\nfancy us getting to the Sacred Tree.
Your advance stops here. I have my\norders, and I WILL carry them out!
Now, strike them down, androids! Fight 'til\nyour bodies crumble to dust, in service of\nhis hallowed vision!
The androids are all converging at once!
No matter how many times we take them\ndown, they just keep getting back up.\nHow can he make them fight like this?!
There's no end to them! ▷Laxi, we have\nto do something, or our maestro is...◁
It's over, false prince. Your life is forfeit,\nfor the future of our new Faerie Kingdom!
Mascula. Engage Eden mode at once.\nI need your support.
▷Another life is about to be stolen...\nright in front of my eyes!◁
MASCULA! Repeat, requesting immediate\nEden mode activation!
What?! Don't tell me you intend to\nenter the fray yourself!
Are you giving up your ideals?
▷I have my own way of ＂fighting.＂ I was\nso happy when you acknowledged that.◁
▷Just as you say, adherence to one's\nvalues is a legitimate path to tread.\nBut that takes a strong heart.◁
▷Strong enough to accept every cost,\nevery sacrifice...and stay the course,\ncome what may.◁
▷I'm afraid I'm just too weak for that.◁
▷I can't bear to watch a life be lost.◁
Condition clear. Checking Orchis System.\nSystem clear. Mascula...
Hm? It's the faulty puppet from before.
Cut me down, if you can. I do not fear\na blade held by trembling hands.
Ah! The androids have ceased function!
Yes... It was a close call, but I'm fine.
Thank the Goddess...\nI'm so relieved you're safe!
Whew, that one had me sweatin'.\nIf those bots hadn't shut down...
I shudder to think of it. So, Mascula\nstopped the one controlling them, then?
We owe you a huge debt.\nThank you so much, Mascu—
Crying? No, this is... The last command I\nexecuted put considerable strain on my\ncircuitry...
So the...the coolant fluid pumped through\nthis body to prevent overheating is being\nexpelled, and—
Such a volume of coolant is usually not\nrequired, unless the strain is exceptionally\nsevere.
Yes. Even having resolved myself thus,\nit seems I underestimated how difficult\nit would be to...to kill.
Hey. Mascula. I'm no expert in android\nphysiology—er, technology?—but...
Isn't that the same as crying because\nyou're sad?
I'm...crying out of sadness?\nThen... Then these are...
